  "texts": [
    "IntroductionVisual grounding (VG), the task of associating natural language descriptions with specific image regions, is crucial for bridging visual perception and language understanding.",
    "This capability underpins numerous downstream tasks, such as visual question answering, human-robot interaction, and interactive image retrieval.",
    "Traditional VG benchmarks, including Referring Expression Comprehension (REC) (Yu et al. 2016; Mao et al.",
    "2016) and Referring Expression Segmentation (RES), typically rely on meticulously annotated datasets containing tens of thousands of image-object pairs.",
    "This limited scale contrasts sharply with contemporary object detection datasets, which commonly offer millions of annotated instances (Lin et al."
  ]
}